-- CTC Media’s Moscow Audience Falls in Week to April 29, TNS Says
-- B y   H a l i a   P a v l i v a
-- 2012-05-02T14:43:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-02/ctc-media-s-moscow-audience-falls-in-week-to-april-29-tns-says.html
CTC Media Inc. (CTCM) ’s average daily share
of viewers in Moscow aged 18-years-old and above fell to 5.4
percent in the week to April 29, knocking it down one level in
the audience rankings, data compiled by TNS-Global show.  The share of viewers in Moscow for the CTC TV channel, the
Nasdaq-listed Russian media company’s biggest source of revenue,
fell from 6 percent in the week to April 22, data researcher
TNS-Global said in an e-mail today. NTV Television, Pervyi
Kanal, Rossiya-1, TNT and REN TV all ranked ahead of CTC among
Moscow viewers, TNS-Global data show.  The average daily audience among viewers four-years-old and
over in Moscow for CTC fell to 6.2 percent in the week to April
29 from 6.6 percent in the previous week, the data show. CTC
retained its fifth rank in this category of viewers in the week
to April 29, while NTV Television, Pervyi Kanal, Rossiya-1 and
TNT all scored ahead of CTC, TNS-Global said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
